1
00:01:41,685 --> 00:01:43,938
We're done!

2
00:01:59,219 --> 00:02:01,164
I hope I'll make you up
for your wedding.

3
00:02:01,306 --> 00:02:03,358
You first!

4
00:02:27,192 --> 00:02:29,339
Layale, listen darling.

5
00:02:29,488 --> 00:02:32,263
I have an audition
for a major ad and I'm late.

6
00:02:32,410 --> 00:02:34,878
Please let me in before the redhead.

7
00:02:39,021 --> 00:02:40,480
Hello, Soussou.

8
00:02:40,622 --> 00:02:42,354
- How are you?
- Fine.

9
00:02:42,535 --> 00:02:44,896
What will it be today?

10
00:02:45,075 --> 00:02:47,780
Lots of volume, like a fluffy cat.

11
00:02:47,928 --> 00:02:49,316
For Sunday.

12
00:02:49,493 --> 00:02:50,632
What's on Sunday?

13
00:02:50,781 --> 00:02:54,600
We might bury my sister-in-law.

14
00:02:54,747 --> 00:02:57,737
She's dying, she won't last long.

15
00:02:58,157 --> 00:02:59,746
But everything is ready.

16
00:03:00,523 --> 00:03:02,599
I bought two pretty trays...

17
00:03:02,749 --> 00:03:04,967
...for serving coffee and cigarettes.

18
00:03:05,115 --> 00:03:08,140
Handmade, at a very good price.

19
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:11,333
And what a dress I got her!

20
00:03:11,516 --> 00:03:15,099
With lace, especially around the collar.

21
00:03:15,274 --> 00:03:18,264
Then I took it to the tailor...

22
00:03:18,405 --> 00:03:20,173
...to take it in.

23
00:03:21,258 --> 00:03:24,283
Layale, it's for you.

24
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:34,055
Hello.

25
00:03:38,654 --> 00:03:39,828
Okay.

26
00:03:39,976 --> 00:03:43,001
Okay, my love.

27
00:03:46,621 --> 00:03:48,602
Soussou, I have to run.

28
00:03:48,744 --> 00:03:52,006
Nisrine will look after you. Okay?

29
00:03:52,154 --> 00:03:53,470
This is outrageous!

30
00:03:53,615 --> 00:03:57,220
Nisrine, look after the shop.
I won't be long.

31
00:04:00,434 --> 00:04:01,822
Nisrine.

32
00:04:21,796 --> 00:04:25,692
- Lili. Lili, what are you doing?
- Working.

33
00:04:25,692 --> 00:04:27,282
What?

34
00:04:27,432 --> 00:04:28,535
What are you doing?

35
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:31,117
- I'm looking for a piece of paper.
- What paper?

36
00:04:31,260 --> 00:04:32,505
My piece of paper.

37
00:04:32,650 --> 00:04:34,145
Okay, out of the way.

38
00:04:35,713 --> 00:04:37,860
I'll give you another one.

39
00:04:40,305 --> 00:04:41,894
But!

40
00:04:42,044 --> 00:04:44,618
Take this one, it's better.

41
00:04:45,037 --> 00:04:46,140
Take it.

42
00:04:46,289 --> 00:04:49,029
- I don't want it.
- It's much nicer.

43
00:04:50,186 --> 00:04:52,404
Look how nice these are.

44
00:04:52,552 --> 00:04:54,663
There's plenty.
Forget the other one.

45
00:04:54,848 --> 00:04:58,453
- Where are you going?
- I'm going to Hell, where else?

46
00:04:59,649 --> 00:05:01,903
Go now.

47
00:05:45,713 --> 00:05:46,744
Hello, Miss.

48
00:05:47,035 --> 00:05:48,316
Hello.

49
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:50,999
You'd look prettier with the seatbelt on.

50
00:05:51,141 --> 00:05:53,846
I can't, it suffocates me.

51
00:05:53,994 --> 00:05:56,912
Truth be told, you're absolutely right.

52
00:05:57,056 --> 00:06:01,362
But public safety requires it.

53
00:06:01,509 --> 00:06:04,771
And if I don't put it on?

54
00:06:06,032 --> 00:06:08,606
I'll have to...

55
00:06:08,746 --> 00:06:10,442
...fine you.

56
00:06:11,877 --> 00:06:14,652
As if I'm not fined enough?

57
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,160
Better now?

58
00:06:17,652 --> 00:06:18,826
Satisfied?

59
00:06:19,392 --> 00:06:21,194
Marvelous.

60
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:24,851
- Can I go now?
- Drive safely.

61
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:30,096
Thank you.

62
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:54,914
- What's up?
- Oh, my God!

63
00:07:16,938 --> 00:07:19,156
Do you want a snack?

64
00:07:22,643 --> 00:07:24,588
Your shirt is pretty.

65
00:07:24,731 --> 00:07:27,233
Did she give it to you?

66
00:07:29,254 --> 00:07:32,932
I won't leave until you fix my hair.

67
00:07:33,115 --> 00:07:35,441
- What is this?
- Volume.

68
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:38,717
You call this volume?
Do you like it?

69
00:07:38,856 --> 00:07:40,873
Would you go out looking like this?

70
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:45,564
- What's up?
- Shut them up...

71
00:07:45,710 --> 00:07:48,450
...before I lose my temper
and hurt someone.

72
00:07:48,599 --> 00:07:50,472
We need to close.

73
00:07:52,947 --> 00:07:54,928
What's this pin for?

74
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:58,130
- It's chic.
- You consider this chic?

75
00:07:58,270 --> 00:08:01,116
What's wrong?
Aren't you late for the audition?

76
00:08:01,262 --> 00:08:04,453
My hair doesn't resemble
the haircut in the magazine.

77
00:08:04,602 --> 00:08:06,405
Look closely at the picture.

78
00:08:06,551 --> 00:08:08,982
Can't you see that the model
is your daughter's age?

79
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:12,530
Shut up and go inside.
That's enough.

80
00:08:12,674 --> 00:08:15,449
What's wrong?
It's looks great.

81
00:08:15,596 --> 00:08:17,328
You think this is great, Layale?

82
00:08:17,475 --> 00:08:20,251
My hair has no volume.

83
00:08:20,398 --> 00:08:24,217
See how she glued these?
I look old and cockeyed.

84
00:08:24,363 --> 00:08:26,439
Like a femme fatale.

85
00:08:26,591 --> 00:08:28,773
Shut your trap!

86
00:08:28,957 --> 00:08:32,503
What does she want?
To get rid of me?

87
00:08:32,645 --> 00:08:34,032
No, to be your loyal slave.

88
00:08:34,175 --> 00:08:35,907
Will you shut up?

89
00:08:36,089 --> 00:08:37,785
It's too hot in here.

90
00:08:37,932 --> 00:08:40,506
Don't be cheap, turn on the AC.

91
00:08:40,681 --> 00:08:43,350
The electrical fuse might blow up.

92
00:08:43,499 --> 00:08:46,097
- Shut up.
- Switch off the fridge.

93
00:08:46,282 --> 00:08:49,272
Forget this tape, it's useless.

94
00:08:49,413 --> 00:08:51,073
Yeah, you're right.

95
00:08:51,224 --> 00:08:54,319
Why do you insist on using it?

96
00:08:54,981 --> 00:08:59,322
I'll tie your hair in a way...

97
00:08:59,468 --> 00:09:02,006
...that will lift your eyes up
without the tape.

98
00:09:04,166 --> 00:09:07,771
You'll look younger.
Then, we take off this pin.

99
00:09:07,958 --> 00:09:10,496
- Look how gorgeous.
- You think so?

100
00:09:10,637 --> 00:09:13,898
You're dazzling.
Like an orchid.

101
00:09:15,438 --> 00:09:18,285
Rima, Johnny Bravo's here.

102
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:21,241
Thank God we're closed.

103
00:09:21,979 --> 00:09:23,083
Hi, girls.

104
00:09:23,266 --> 00:09:25,769
Hello. Good evening.

105
00:09:33,495 --> 00:09:34,526
How are you, Bassam?

106
00:09:34,678 --> 00:09:38,426
If they like your hair,
tell them I did it.

107
00:09:40,627 --> 00:09:44,376
Good luck with the audition.

108
00:09:44,594 --> 00:09:47,167
Rima, take care of the shop.

109
00:09:47,308 --> 00:09:49,881
- Yeah, okay.
- Bye.

110
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:21,880
Hello, Auntie Rose.
How are you?

111
00:10:22,030 --> 00:10:24,735
- Fine, and you?
- All is well.

112
00:10:24,883 --> 00:10:26,994
How are you, Lili?

113
00:10:27,388 --> 00:10:30,578
I've got some aprons that need fixing.

114
00:10:30,727 --> 00:10:33,123
Put them on the table.

115
00:10:33,302 --> 00:10:35,935
Stay for coffee.
We'll have a chat.

116
00:10:36,086 --> 00:10:39,455
Some other time.
I have a bus to catch.

117
00:10:39,634 --> 00:10:41,223
Bye, Lili.

118
00:10:41,373 --> 00:10:43,662
Lili, she's saying goodbye.

119
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:45,612
Bye, bye, bye.

120
00:10:45,758 --> 00:10:47,288
Okay, I'm off.

121
00:10:47,463 --> 00:10:50,618
Goodnight. Thank you.

122
00:10:51,881 --> 00:10:55,071
Lili, why are you acting this way?

123
00:10:56,195 --> 00:10:58,484
She was talking to you.

124
00:10:58,630 --> 00:11:00,777
You want to scare the customers away?

125
00:11:00,926 --> 00:11:03,144
What are you doing?

126
00:12:24,636 --> 00:12:26,889
Do I look better now?

127
00:12:27,419 --> 00:12:30,610
You'd look better
without the chewing gum.

128
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:42,582
Welcome, it's a great honor.
Behold our future bride.

129
00:12:42,971 --> 00:12:44,039
It's a great pleasure.

130
00:12:44,189 --> 00:12:47,700
You made us happy.
Bless you.

131
00:12:50,590 --> 00:12:52,013
Are you mad?

132
00:12:52,191 --> 00:12:54,823
No one can see us.

133
00:13:03,289 --> 00:13:05,472
My God.

134
00:13:05,621 --> 00:13:07,839
You're so handsome.

135
00:13:08,125 --> 00:13:09,785
Let me do the dishes.

136
00:13:09,934 --> 00:13:11,702
You've been up since this morning.

137
00:13:13,553 --> 00:13:15,913
No, let me do it.

138
00:13:17,067 --> 00:13:18,834
I'll do it!

139
00:13:29,974 --> 00:13:31,777
Okay, dear?

140
00:13:32,132 --> 00:13:35,014
How is work?
Everything is fine?

141
00:13:35,159 --> 00:13:36,368
Hello.

142
00:13:36,933 --> 00:13:38,392
Is there a problem?

143
00:13:38,568 --> 00:13:40,122
No, everything's great.

144
00:13:40,308 --> 00:13:41,339
Please, feel at home.

145
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:44,546
Thank you.

146
00:14:00,174 --> 00:14:02,321
I cannot speak louder.

147
00:14:02,470 --> 00:14:05,103
My little brother's asleep.

148
00:14:11,446 --> 00:14:14,637
I can't go to the living room.
My parents will hear me.

149
00:14:17,570 --> 00:14:20,903
Wait, I'll go to the bathroom.

150
00:14:28,146 --> 00:14:30,815
Can you hear me better?

151
00:14:31,382 --> 00:14:33,291
How many times must we talk about it?

152
00:14:33,435 --> 00:14:37,183
I don't feel myself.

153
00:14:58,136 --> 00:15:00,462
What's his problem?

154
00:15:12,123 --> 00:15:13,333
Hello.

155
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:14,511
Hello.

156
00:15:14,628 --> 00:15:15,944
A problem with the car?

157
00:15:17,028 --> 00:15:19,626
No. Is there a problem?

158
00:15:19,777 --> 00:15:21,473
The lady is your wife?

159
00:15:23,883 --> 00:15:26,456
The lady is my fiancйe.

160
00:15:26,632 --> 00:15:28,814
Your fiancйe.

161
00:15:29,171 --> 00:15:31,638
What are you doing
in the middle of the night?

162
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:35,009
We were at a party.
Now we're having a chat.

163
00:15:35,156 --> 00:15:37,409
And I'm about to walk her home.

164
00:15:37,590 --> 00:15:39,666
Why don't you chat at her place?

165
00:15:39,818 --> 00:15:41,691
This is an indecent activity.

166
00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:44,195
Two people talking in the street...

167
00:15:44,340 --> 00:15:46,107
...is an indecent activity?

168
00:15:46,289 --> 00:15:48,471
Who can prove she lives here?

169
00:15:49,768 --> 00:15:51,357
Her parents live here.

170
00:15:51,507 --> 00:15:55,470
Do you want us to go up
and check it out together?

171
00:15:55,613 --> 00:15:57,071
Lower your voice.

172
00:15:57,213 --> 00:15:59,645
Quit it, I'm talking.

173
00:15:59,822 --> 00:16:01,376
Who can prove she's your fiancйe?

174
00:16:01,527 --> 00:16:05,204
Instead of catching criminals,
you're harassing us?

175
00:16:05,355 --> 00:16:06,458
Exactly!

176
00:16:06,641 --> 00:16:08,895
Help me, God!
He doesn't want to understand.

177
00:16:09,043 --> 00:16:11,296
- And now what?
- Your ID.

178
00:16:11,477 --> 00:16:13,553
- Give him the ID.
- No way.

179
00:16:13,705 --> 00:16:17,287
Give him the ID.
Don't make a scene.

180
00:16:17,462 --> 00:16:18,920
Never!

181
00:16:19,062 --> 00:16:21,351
What a stubborn mule.

182
00:16:21,532 --> 00:16:24,202
Comply, or get out of the car.

183
00:16:24,351 --> 00:16:26,569
My God, I'm always misunderstood.

184
00:16:26,751 --> 00:16:29,847
Get out of the vehicle, please.

185
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:31,754
I won't get out! You get in!

186
00:16:32,631 --> 00:16:37,779
"The policeman having insisted...

187
00:16:39,033 --> 00:16:40,907
...several times...

188
00:16:41,538 --> 00:16:45,465
...that the driver..."

189
00:16:46,896 --> 00:16:49,043
What's his name again, our "Romeo"?

190
00:16:49,192 --> 00:16:51,446
Bassam the Bragger.

191
00:16:52,671 --> 00:16:55,897
Bragger! Bragger.

192
00:16:56,985 --> 00:17:01,612
"...to get out of the vehicle..."

193
00:17:03,108 --> 00:17:05,053
What did he say?

194
00:17:05,127 --> 00:17:07,559
"Even God won't get me out".

195
00:17:08,641 --> 00:17:10,622
God?

196
00:17:18,417 --> 00:17:22,166
"Even God won't get me out...

197
00:17:22,940 --> 00:17:26,166
...of the vehicle."

198
00:17:27,881 --> 00:17:29,197
He's one strong guy.

199
00:17:31,221 --> 00:17:34,411
You know that we have enough
reasons to send you to jail?

200
00:17:34,561 --> 00:17:37,193
That'll make your day.

201
00:17:44,024 --> 00:17:47,879
<i>Oh, yes, our beautiful bride</i>

202
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:52,023
<i>Oh yes, Bassam is at her feet</i>

203
00:17:52,165 --> 00:17:55,011
<i>Oh yes, for you we shall sing</i>

204
00:17:57,732 --> 00:17:58,835
<i>Walk proud</i>

205
00:17:58,984 --> 00:18:01,938
<i>Our lovely and pretty bride</i>

206
00:18:02,115 --> 00:18:06,148
<i>If that night, Bassam didn 't mess up</i>

207
00:18:06,326 --> 00:18:08,437
<i>And the police didn 't rub</i>
<i>His face in the mud</i>

208
00:18:08,622 --> 00:18:10,354
<i>And your father didn't threaten him</i>

209
00:18:10,501 --> 00:18:13,039
<i>Your wedding day</i>
<i>Would have never come so soon!</i>

210
00:18:16,867 --> 00:18:20,865
<i>Walk proud, my lovely bride</i>

211
00:18:21,042 --> 00:18:24,138
<i>The most beautiful rose</i>
<i>In the garden</i>

212
00:18:30,088 --> 00:18:32,105
Help! Help me!

213
00:18:34,193 --> 00:18:37,668
Please, help me!

214
00:18:38,090 --> 00:18:40,521
- Please let go.
- No way!

215
00:18:40,665 --> 00:18:41,696
I want them.

216
00:18:41,848 --> 00:18:45,109
Even if I must lie
in the middle of the road.

217
00:18:45,292 --> 00:18:48,838
Go back, please. Let go.

218
00:18:48,980 --> 00:18:51,720
I'll call a policeman.
I've had enough!

219
00:18:51,868 --> 00:18:53,885
But I am the police.

220
00:18:55,208 --> 00:18:56,737
He deserves it.

221
00:18:56,877 --> 00:18:59,166
- Although he's cute.
- Cute? Him?

222
00:18:59,313 --> 00:19:01,045
You never like anybody?

223
00:19:01,192 --> 00:19:04,312
Enough. Without him,
we'd still be at the police station.

224
00:19:04,462 --> 00:19:06,371
Even God wouldn't
get him out of the car.

225
00:19:06,515 --> 00:19:08,768
These are parking tickets.
Why do you want them?

226
00:19:08,915 --> 00:19:12,664
They are from my fiancй.

227
00:19:12,812 --> 00:19:14,092
Your fiancй?

228
00:19:15,178 --> 00:19:17,052
Come here.

229
00:19:17,231 --> 00:19:19,413
My God, your grip is as powerful
as a crab's claw!

230
00:19:19,562 --> 00:19:21,638
What's the matter, my dear Lili?

231
00:19:21,789 --> 00:19:23,865
He's torturing me.

232
00:19:24,015 --> 00:19:25,889
- What's going on?
- She's collecting tickets.

233
00:19:26,033 --> 00:19:28,951
You don't want that?
That's better, isn't it?

234
00:19:29,095 --> 00:19:31,941
- I don't want it.
- Take a flower.

235
00:19:32,087 --> 00:19:33,641
I don't want it!

236
00:19:33,827 --> 00:19:35,487
What is she doing?

237
00:19:35,810 --> 00:19:38,621
She is stealing the tickets!

238
00:19:38,767 --> 00:19:41,685
Thank you for what you did last night.

239
00:19:41,828 --> 00:19:43,525
It's nothing.

240
00:19:43,707 --> 00:19:45,439
If you hadn't been there...

241
00:19:45,586 --> 00:19:49,335
You know, I didn't do much.

242
00:19:49,483 --> 00:19:54,383
You could drop by our salon sometime.

243
00:19:55,050 --> 00:19:57,683
- We'll give you special treatment.
- One day, I will.

244
00:19:57,867 --> 00:19:59,564
Nisrine, come here!

245
00:19:59,746 --> 00:20:02,487
All the girls will be at your service.

246
00:20:02,634 --> 00:20:04,615
Goodbye. We'll be expecting you.

247
00:20:17,456 --> 00:20:20,089
You think you're stronger
than the policeman?

248
00:20:20,239 --> 00:20:22,527
Go inside now.

249
00:20:22,674 --> 00:20:23,990
I won't.

250
00:20:24,135 --> 00:20:25,238
Stop. I'm working.

251
00:20:25,388 --> 00:20:27,676
Oh, really! You're working?

252
00:20:27,858 --> 00:20:31,441
You do nothing but follow me.

253
00:20:32,068 --> 00:20:33,099
Hello, ladies.

254
00:20:33,251 --> 00:20:34,567
Hello. Welcome.

255
00:20:34,713 --> 00:20:37,215
Don't talk to her!
Come, let me give you some love.

256
00:20:37,356 --> 00:20:40,345
Go inside.

257
00:20:40,523 --> 00:20:41,803
Ma'am, could you, please...

258
00:20:41,949 --> 00:20:43,823
Go in, so I can understand.

259
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:47,929
How can you understand him?
You can't even understand me.

260
00:20:48,072 --> 00:20:51,405
- He's American.
- Shut up. Let me find out what he wants.

261
00:20:51,551 --> 00:20:54,327
He wants me to run away with him.

262
00:20:54,508 --> 00:20:58,257
Go inside, you're embarrassing me.
I want to know what he wants.

263
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:01,560
Go play with the rubbish
you've been collecting.

264
00:21:02,754 --> 00:21:04,830
Don't come out again.

265
00:21:06,859 --> 00:21:10,406
There. That's the vest.

266
00:21:10,547 --> 00:21:11,651
The jacket.

267
00:21:11,869 --> 00:21:15,274
It's too big, it needs fixing.

268
00:21:15,419 --> 00:21:17,495
- Oh, you want to fix it?
- Yes.

269
00:21:17,645 --> 00:21:20,350
The trousers need shortening.

270
00:21:20,498 --> 00:21:21,601
That's fine. Go change.

271
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:24,490
Alright. Go in and try it on.

272
00:21:24,673 --> 00:21:28,777
- Try.
- Alright.

273
00:21:28,918 --> 00:21:31,029
Thank you.

274
00:22:09,659 --> 00:22:13,063
<i>My darling likes to go for a stroll</i>

275
00:22:13,242 --> 00:22:14,772
<i>In the evening, he says</i>
<i>Let's go</i>

276
00:22:15,330 --> 00:22:20,407
<i>If I say no, I'm in trouble</i>

277
00:22:20,549 --> 00:22:22,493
<i>Welcome, my prince</i>

278
00:22:23,958 --> 00:22:25,488
Lili, what are you doing?

279
00:22:25,663 --> 00:22:27,680
You keep on sewing.

280
00:22:29,525 --> 00:22:31,019
Sorry.

281
00:22:31,195 --> 00:22:33,448
Good morning, sir.
How are you?

282
00:22:33,630 --> 00:22:37,735
Where have you been, my love?

283
00:22:47,825 --> 00:22:50,327
Hello, Auntie Rose.

284
00:22:50,678 --> 00:22:51,994
Here are the aprons.

285
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:54,986
Come in, don't stay by the door.

286
00:22:55,131 --> 00:22:58,121
No, I can't.
I left Lili by herself.

287
00:22:58,262 --> 00:23:00,279
Don't worry about Lili.

288
00:23:00,454 --> 00:23:02,921
Come in for a hairdo.
We're not busy.

289
00:23:03,064 --> 00:23:06,184
- No, no.
- Come on in.

290
00:23:06,334 --> 00:23:09,039
I must go, she's alone.

291
00:23:09,188 --> 00:23:11,264
Your hair needs a good brushing.

292
00:23:11,414 --> 00:23:13,810
Come on in, we're having coffee.

293
00:23:14,407 --> 00:23:16,589
Come in, we need
to find you a husband.

294
00:23:17,328 --> 00:23:18,573
You're a bit late.

295
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:21,353
You're still beautiful, come in.

296
00:23:21,503 --> 00:23:25,014
No, Lili's all by herself. I must go.

297
00:23:41,648 --> 00:23:42,680
Hello.

298
00:23:49,128 --> 00:23:52,769
Sorry, I came without an appointment.
Can I get my hair done?

299
00:25:05,461 --> 00:25:08,581
- Something's bothering you?
- Not at all.

300
00:25:08,731 --> 00:25:11,578
I was just walking by.
I decided to come in.

301
00:25:11,724 --> 00:25:14,156
I had nothing to do.

302
00:25:15,412 --> 00:25:18,152
I'm glad that you came.

303
00:26:15,045 --> 00:26:16,954
Go on, run.

304
00:27:25,359 --> 00:27:28,384
Handsome young man.
Don't forget!

305
00:27:28,525 --> 00:27:31,965
Pick up the ones under the car.

306
00:27:32,769 --> 00:27:36,589
And you, sweetheart.
Pick up the two papers over there.

307
00:27:36,736 --> 00:27:38,680
Put them in the basket.

308
00:27:38,823 --> 00:27:42,750
God bless you and keep you safe.

309
00:27:53,157 --> 00:27:56,763
Yes, put them in there.

310
00:27:59,003 --> 00:28:01,363
I want to see what he wrote to me.

311
00:28:01,507 --> 00:28:02,538
What?

312
00:28:02,691 --> 00:28:06,095
He loves me very much.
He wrote me all these letters.

313
00:28:06,239 --> 00:28:07,936
- Thank you, dear.
- Okay, bye.

314
00:28:11,249 --> 00:28:12,838
Don't be long!

315
00:28:43,049 --> 00:28:45,101
Hello, my love.

316
00:28:51,469 --> 00:28:52,857
Hello.

317
00:28:53,626 --> 00:28:55,393
Hello, sunshine.

318
00:28:55,574 --> 00:28:58,314
You forgot your wallet.

319
00:28:59,470 --> 00:29:01,380
I was expecting your call.

320
00:29:02,253 --> 00:29:03,843
What?

321
00:29:04,341 --> 00:29:07,046
I swear, I've been waiting for an hour.

322
00:29:07,195 --> 00:29:08,724
Ask Joseph.

323
00:29:10,743 --> 00:29:12,688
Okay, stop fooling around.

324
00:29:12,831 --> 00:29:14,289
When can you pick it up?

325
00:29:15,962 --> 00:29:19,924
Now I'm busy.
I'm having my coffee.

326
00:29:20,972 --> 00:29:23,854
And Joseph is foreseeing my future.

327
00:29:26,260 --> 00:29:29,486
He sees a chair and a beautiful girl.

328
00:29:29,669 --> 00:29:33,145
She's at the window.
She's looking at me without seeing me.

329
00:29:39,481 --> 00:29:40,869
I swear.

330
00:29:41,569 --> 00:29:44,238
There's even a fly on my forehead.

331
00:29:45,257 --> 00:29:48,377
She parks in forbidden areas...

332
00:29:48,527 --> 00:29:52,240
...to tease the policeman
who's admiring her...

333
00:29:52,876 --> 00:29:54,952
...instead of fining her.

334
00:29:59,382 --> 00:30:02,087
You find it funny!

335
00:30:04,217 --> 00:30:07,728
Okay, goodbye.

336
00:31:20,621 --> 00:31:21,652
Anything else?

337
00:31:21,839 --> 00:31:24,864
Can you sign here, please?

338
00:31:26,222 --> 00:31:29,591
- Where?
- Here, please.

339
00:31:32,972 --> 00:31:34,003
That's it?

340
00:31:34,154 --> 00:31:37,974
Here also. New regulations.

341
00:31:38,608 --> 00:31:40,411
- Anything else?
- Thank you.

342
00:31:40,557 --> 00:31:42,573
Let's go.

343
00:31:45,149 --> 00:31:47,722
- Can I drop you off somewhere?
- What?

344
00:31:47,933 --> 00:31:51,574
- Drop you off?
- No, thanks. Don't bother.

345
00:32:21,610 --> 00:32:24,457
Tarek, answer.

346
00:32:24,603 --> 00:32:28,351
Tarek, answer!

347
00:32:31,422 --> 00:32:32,774
Hurry up, Lйa.

348
00:32:35,736 --> 00:32:37,016
Yes, Dad.

349
00:32:37,615 --> 00:32:39,382
Mom?

350
00:32:40,642 --> 00:32:42,302
She's not here.

351
00:32:42,451 --> 00:32:43,482
I don't know.

352
00:32:46,870 --> 00:32:48,779
Smoking a joint next door.

353
00:32:49,583 --> 00:32:51,527
Stupid! Damn you!

354
00:32:56,959 --> 00:32:59,532
What's the matter? I'm busy.

355
00:32:59,673 --> 00:33:02,663
I'm busy in the kitchen.
What do you want?

356
00:33:02,804 --> 00:33:04,682
What?

357
00:33:04,682 --> 00:33:07,185
Why promise the kids...

358
00:33:07,327 --> 00:33:09,924
...and then change your mind?

359
00:33:10,111 --> 00:33:12,743
Good for you.
Okay, leave me alone.

360
00:33:12,894 --> 00:33:14,696
Okay, goodbye.

361
00:33:15,398 --> 00:33:17,130
What an idiot!

362
00:33:17,277 --> 00:33:19,744
And you two, out of my sight!

363
00:33:19,887 --> 00:33:22,140
Your father is busy.

364
00:33:22,287 --> 00:33:24,957
He's taking his girlfriend to the beach.

365
00:33:34,256 --> 00:33:36,023
Hello.

366
00:33:37,735 --> 00:33:40,926
I want to have my hair done.

367
00:33:41,075 --> 00:33:42,842
Of course, come in.

368
00:33:45,807 --> 00:33:48,927
- Hello.
- Good morning. Welcome.

369
00:34:46,553 --> 00:34:50,372
Start the generator,
I need to use the blow dryer.

370
00:35:00,609 --> 00:35:02,138
Sorry it took me so long.

371
00:35:03,114 --> 00:35:04,703
It's okay.

372
00:35:08,716 --> 00:35:11,349
Mr. Charles!

373
00:35:12,090 --> 00:35:15,352
Mr. Charles, tell her to let me out.

374
00:35:18,074 --> 00:35:20,150
Why are you so stubborn?

375
00:35:20,301 --> 00:35:22,377
Stubborn as a mule!

376
00:35:23,223 --> 00:35:25,026
You old bag!

377
00:35:25,206 --> 00:35:27,804
In your dreams, I'll let you out!

378
00:35:27,955 --> 00:35:29,544
I'm going to kill her.

379
00:35:33,835 --> 00:35:37,417
There are people
expecting me for dinner.

380
00:35:37,558 --> 00:35:39,290
Expecting you?

381
00:35:39,436 --> 00:35:41,583
In Hell, yes.

382
00:35:41,733 --> 00:35:43,845
You wait and see.

383
00:35:44,029 --> 00:35:47,813
The plane is about to take off.
It's getting dark.

384
00:35:47,996 --> 00:35:50,072
She wants to travel now.

385
00:35:50,222 --> 00:35:52,583
I'll send you up to Heaven, alright.

386
00:35:53,701 --> 00:35:56,299
I'm going to tell the neighbors.

387
00:35:57,737 --> 00:36:01,283
They'll eat you alive.

388
00:36:04,208 --> 00:36:05,940
Rose!

389
00:36:06,156 --> 00:36:09,834
Damn whoever gave you that name.

390
00:36:12,349 --> 00:36:14,330
Excuse me.

391
00:36:15,620 --> 00:36:17,565
Wait till I get my hands on you.

392
00:36:17,708 --> 00:36:21,254
If you drive the customers away,
how will we survive? Go upstairs!

393
00:36:21,396 --> 00:36:25,001
- The plane is taking off.
- What plane? Where to?

394
00:36:25,153 --> 00:36:26,540
I'm expected for dinner.

395
00:36:26,683 --> 00:36:29,803
Yes, everybody's expecting you.

396
00:36:29,954 --> 00:36:33,952
If you drive them away,
how will we live?

397
00:36:42,688 --> 00:36:45,013
I'm sorry, sir.

398
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:48,805
Sorry.

399
00:36:51,072 --> 00:36:54,168
Are the trousers okay?

400
00:36:58,971 --> 00:37:02,411
I'd like them a little shorter, please.

401
00:37:02,589 --> 00:37:05,436
- Shorter?
- Yes. I like it.

402
00:37:06,554 --> 00:37:10,030
- Shorter? Like this?
- Yes.

403
00:37:10,174 --> 00:37:13,020
Nice, isn't it?

404
00:37:16,296 --> 00:37:19,595
Just what I needed.
Another crazy fool.

405
00:37:34,040 --> 00:37:35,071
Walid.

406
00:37:36,510 --> 00:37:38,836
Can you call me from the land line?

407
00:37:38,981 --> 00:37:40,012
I'm too tired.

408
00:37:40,164 --> 00:37:42,276
I need to check if my mobile is working.

409
00:37:42,460 --> 00:37:45,485
Do as your sister says.

410
00:37:53,559 --> 00:37:55,112
Okay, it's working.

411
00:38:06,118 --> 00:38:09,072
- Where are you going?
- I'll be back.

412
00:38:25,045 --> 00:38:27,927
Rabih, it's Layale.

413
00:38:29,359 --> 00:38:32,834
Rabih. Can you hear me?

414
00:39:03,977 --> 00:39:07,097
Layale. Layale.

415
00:39:07,247 --> 00:39:08,278
Yes?

416
00:39:08,430 --> 00:39:10,684
The fan's batteries are dead.

417
00:39:10,866 --> 00:39:12,942
Do you have any?

418
00:39:21,617 --> 00:39:24,048
Hello! Come in.

419
00:39:26,765 --> 00:39:30,585
Look in the cup, there's a white horse!

420
00:39:30,766 --> 00:39:32,355
Do you know what it means?

421
00:39:32,507 --> 00:39:34,060
You'll be married soon.

422
00:39:35,324 --> 00:39:37,233
Are you hiding secrets from us?

423
00:39:37,794 --> 00:39:39,491
Hiding secrets from your mother?

424
00:39:39,639 --> 00:39:41,821
You believe this nonsense, Mom?

425
00:39:42,005 --> 00:39:43,665
Yes, of course!

426
00:39:46,423 --> 00:39:48,748
Make a wish now.

427
00:39:54,077 --> 00:39:57,446
There's a husband, look at the ring!

428
00:39:57,625 --> 00:39:59,772
Look how it sparkles.

429
00:40:00,757 --> 00:40:03,497
That's good.
She's going to get married.

430
00:40:03,645 --> 00:40:05,448
That's for sure,
you're going to be happy.

431
00:40:05,593 --> 00:40:07,740
You believe this rubbish?

432
00:40:08,585 --> 00:40:10,839
Things she's told me have come true...

433
00:40:11,021 --> 00:40:13,073
We'll eat cakes.

434
00:40:13,213 --> 00:40:15,609
We'll rejoice.

435
00:41:42,245 --> 00:41:46,135
Hi, my name's Jamale Tarabay.
I have two children.

436
00:41:46,420 --> 00:41:48,496
Turn the board around.

437
00:41:48,716 --> 00:41:50,898
I can't read it.

438
00:41:52,682 --> 00:41:54,699
My name's Jamale Tarabay...

439
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:56,155
The light's too strong.

440
00:41:56,300 --> 00:41:58,376
Nothing I can do about it.

441
00:41:58,528 --> 00:42:00,604
Look into the camera.

442
00:42:01,936 --> 00:42:05,412
I have two children.
I have many hobbies.

443
00:42:05,555 --> 00:42:07,014
I was an actress.

444
00:42:07,155 --> 00:42:10,002
- Really! What kind of roles?
- Soap operas.

445
00:42:10,182 --> 00:42:11,534
You've never seen me?

446
00:42:11,678 --> 00:42:12,923
Not really.

447
00:42:13,070 --> 00:42:15,573
Series and ads too.

448
00:42:15,715 --> 00:42:17,659
Such as?

449
00:42:18,567 --> 00:42:21,200
Products, detergents, lots of things.

450
00:42:21,350 --> 00:42:24,541
Okay. Now lose the board.

451
00:42:27,196 --> 00:42:29,343
Higher.

452
00:42:29,492 --> 00:42:32,339
Very good. Now the other way.

453
00:42:32,483 --> 00:42:35,224
- How?
- The other way.

454
00:42:35,406 --> 00:42:37,209
Lower your arms.

455
00:42:37,355 --> 00:42:41,104
Tell me about yourself. Right side.

456
00:42:41,252 --> 00:42:43,399
No. Right, darling.

457
00:42:43,548 --> 00:42:45,979
Okay, tell me about yourself.

458
00:42:46,540 --> 00:42:48,616
I have lots of hobbies.

459
00:42:48,766 --> 00:42:50,913
I like music, painting...

460
00:42:51,062 --> 00:42:53,138
Very good.

461
00:42:53,290 --> 00:42:55,271
Other side now.

462
00:42:56,073 --> 00:42:58,813
Other side, please.

463
00:43:00,874 --> 00:43:02,713
Okay. Go on.

464
00:43:02,857 --> 00:43:04,517
Sideways?

465
00:43:04,910 --> 00:43:07,341
Can you walk now?

466
00:43:07,484 --> 00:43:10,509
- That way?
- Please.

467
00:43:28,568 --> 00:43:32,043
Are you a group?

468
00:43:32,187 --> 00:43:33,717
No, just two people.

469
00:43:33,856 --> 00:43:36,976
- Two girls?
- No. My husband and me.

470
00:43:37,162 --> 00:43:40,116
Ah, you're married.

471
00:43:40,327 --> 00:43:44,076
Two people.
A double bed, I guess?

472
00:43:45,129 --> 00:43:47,726
- When for?
- Saturday.

473
00:43:47,912 --> 00:43:50,901
Saturday, just a minute.

474
00:44:02,386 --> 00:44:04,462
Can I have your name?

475
00:44:04,612 --> 00:44:08,087
Rosette Baddour.

476
00:44:08,230 --> 00:44:09,583
Rosette Baddour?

477
00:44:09,762 --> 00:44:12,882
Pretty name, Baddour.

478
00:44:13,032 --> 00:44:16,780
Are you from Beit-Mйry?

479
00:44:16,929 --> 00:44:18,731
I have friends from the Baddour family.

480
00:44:18,877 --> 00:44:20,466
From Beit-Mйry, yes.

481
00:44:20,617 --> 00:44:23,048
Mr. Samir, the owner of the supermarket.

482
00:44:23,191 --> 00:44:26,311
Do you know him?

483
00:44:26,462 --> 00:44:28,336
He's a relative.

484
00:44:28,480 --> 00:44:32,370
By the way, were you living in Canada...

485
00:44:32,515 --> 00:44:34,247
No.

486
00:44:34,394 --> 00:44:35,983
I'm sorry.

487
00:44:36,134 --> 00:44:39,989
I need your ID card, please.

488
00:44:40,378 --> 00:44:43,747
Or any other ID proving that...

489
00:44:44,206 --> 00:44:45,380
...you're married.

490
00:44:45,528 --> 00:44:49,134
These are the regulations.

491
00:44:49,563 --> 00:44:51,022
Just a second...

492
00:44:51,164 --> 00:44:53,417
Take your time.

493
00:45:03,897 --> 00:45:05,700
It's hot. Can we open the window?

494
00:45:05,846 --> 00:45:09,108
No, darling. We can't. Sorry.

495
00:45:09,256 --> 00:45:10,785
Let's continue.

496
00:45:10,925 --> 00:45:13,950
Now face the wall.

497
00:45:16,353 --> 00:45:18,535
Look straight in front of you.

498
00:45:18,788 --> 00:45:21,778
Sideways.

499
00:45:23,033 --> 00:45:25,109
Now look at the wall...

500
00:45:25,259 --> 00:45:28,177
...as if speaking to a friend.

501
00:45:28,530 --> 00:45:31,235
- Recite the script.
- Like this, or towards you?

502
00:45:31,383 --> 00:45:34,088
Your body still, your face towards me.

503
00:45:34,236 --> 00:45:37,427
My body still and my face towards you?

504
00:45:37,576 --> 00:45:39,652
Yesterday, I met my friend.

505
00:45:40,707 --> 00:45:44,385
She told me, "Your face is glowing.
What's your secret?"

506
00:45:44,534 --> 00:45:46,610
Sorry to interrupt...

507
00:45:47,109 --> 00:45:50,134
...but there's something
stuck on your eyebrows.

508
00:45:52,258 --> 00:45:55,449
I told her, " I am using
the new soap Eve."

509
00:45:55,946 --> 00:45:58,164
It has a freshening effect.

510
00:45:58,312 --> 00:46:00,910
Every evening,
I wash my face with it.

511
00:46:07,253 --> 00:46:08,878
Smile.

512
00:46:09,028 --> 00:46:11,804
You should be happy
about your fresh complexion.

513
00:46:11,950 --> 00:46:14,381
My friend congratulated
me on my complexion.

514
00:46:15,221 --> 00:46:19,111
She told me, "What do you do
to have such a radiant complexion?"

515
00:46:19,256 --> 00:46:22,245
"I use a new soap. Eve."

516
00:46:22,387 --> 00:46:24,713
It's very good in the evening.

517
00:46:24,857 --> 00:46:26,934
It is very fresh.

518
00:46:28,233 --> 00:46:30,902
- Come on, go on.
- I can't.

519
00:46:43,855 --> 00:46:46,108
- You'll be with whom?
- Sorry?

520
00:46:46,255 --> 00:46:49,031
Who you're sharing the room with?

521
00:46:49,178 --> 00:46:50,945
With my husband.

522
00:46:51,265 --> 00:46:53,210
Can I have your name?

523
00:46:53,700 --> 00:46:55,989
Liliane Chakkour.

524
00:47:04,069 --> 00:47:07,473
I need an ID card, please.

525
00:47:23,482 --> 00:47:25,984
Hello. Good morning, Pasha.

526
00:47:26,126 --> 00:47:28,558
I'm fine, thank you.

527
00:47:28,700 --> 00:47:30,088
At your service.

528
00:47:31,971 --> 00:47:35,791
It's okay. We'll be there in five minutes.

529
00:47:35,937 --> 00:47:37,989
God be with you.

530
00:47:40,390 --> 00:47:41,493
Good morning.

531
00:47:41,644 --> 00:47:44,419
A morning full of roses and jasmine!

532
00:52:23,108 --> 00:52:25,540
Any cake left?

533
00:52:29,231 --> 00:52:31,449
My God! What's this place?

534
00:52:31,597 --> 00:52:33,056
What?

535
00:52:33,337 --> 00:52:34,761
Oh, my God!

536
00:52:40,574 --> 00:52:43,800
- Why are you so gloomy?
- Look who's talking!

537
00:52:45,793 --> 00:52:47,525
