He likes my style.

807
01:17:30,843 --> 01:17:33,513
That's enough, get out.

808
01:17:34,600 --> 01:17:37,660
Slow down, Rima.
The girl is sick.

809
01:17:37,801 --> 01:17:40,019
I drive as I damn well please.

810
01:17:40,167 --> 01:17:43,322
It's your mouth we should've sewn up.

811
01:17:44,621 --> 01:17:46,565
I don't believe this.

812
01:17:46,708 --> 01:17:51,227
You'd rather I drove into the potholes?

813
01:17:51,370 --> 01:17:54,881
You haven't missed a single one so far!

814
01:17:55,058 --> 01:17:58,533
I just love listening to your complaints.

815
01:17:58,676 --> 01:18:02,152
- You wanted to sit in front!
- All I want is to arrive in one piece.

816
01:18:02,295 --> 01:18:04,999
Do you have an audition or not?

817
01:18:53,160 --> 01:18:56,185
Open, dear.

818
01:18:57,822 --> 01:18:59,174
Rose.

819
01:19:00,258 --> 01:19:04,148
Open, so we can pray together.

820
01:19:04,294 --> 01:19:08,363
I brought you some fish for dinner.

821
01:19:13,340 --> 01:19:15,107
Are you coming?

822
01:19:17,028 --> 01:19:19,281
Poor me.

823
01:19:19,428 --> 01:19:21,824
I'm tired of this life!

824
01:19:32,754 --> 01:19:35,351
Rosa.

825
01:19:36,580 --> 01:19:39,250
My precious.

826
01:19:39,920 --> 01:19:42,767
You want to go to Manara?

827
01:19:42,913 --> 01:19:46,353
Maybe I'll bury you there.

828
01:19:49,384 --> 01:19:53,062
Please, open.

829
01:19:54,324 --> 01:19:57,658
May God send you a nice husband.

830
01:19:58,986 --> 01:20:02,106
I love you, Rose.

831
01:20:30,577 --> 01:20:33,911
Why are you so stubborn?

832
01:20:34,057 --> 01:20:36,239
Why?

833
01:20:36,770 --> 01:20:38,786
Are you deaf?

834
01:20:38,927 --> 01:20:42,047
Shall I take you to an ear doctor?

835
01:21:18,485 --> 01:21:21,819
What a mistake
to let you do this to me!

836
01:21:21,999 --> 01:21:24,016
How can one trust women?
Are you nuts?

837
01:21:25,479 --> 01:21:27,555
Pull the curtains, it's not a show.

838
01:21:27,705 --> 01:21:29,781
You think you're the main attraction?

839
01:21:29,967 --> 01:21:32,778
Why not razors?

840
01:21:32,924 --> 01:21:37,158
One day, you'll miss having all that hair.

841
01:21:37,656 --> 01:21:41,440
I'd like to see you in a skirt,
like a real girl.

842
01:21:41,622 --> 01:21:45,133
You're always complaining. You can't
come to my wedding looking like this.

843
01:21:45,310 --> 01:21:48,430
You have nice legs.
Why do you hide them?

844
01:21:48,615 --> 01:21:51,212
You want me to be like you?
Look at her.

845
01:21:51,363 --> 01:21:53,688
I feel sorry for your husband.

846
01:21:54,286 --> 01:21:55,602
I'll deal with you later.

847
01:21:55,748 --> 01:21:58,345
I can't take it anymore. Take it off.

848
01:21:58,669 --> 01:22:00,781
Two more minutes.

849
01:22:01,801 --> 01:22:05,798
I like his voice more than yours, Rima.

850
01:22:39,167 --> 01:22:41,741
Come on, darling,
get it out of your system.

851
01:22:50,544 --> 01:22:53,082
When it comes to horns,
his horn is really special.

852
01:22:56,911 --> 01:22:58,500
Your taste.

853
01:22:58,651 --> 01:23:00,110
- What's wrong?
- This is naughty.

854
01:23:00,251 --> 01:23:01,567
It's good for a bride.

855
01:23:02,687 --> 01:23:06,233
Mom, stop stuffing
everything in this suitcase.

856
01:23:06,409 --> 01:23:08,876
Who would wear such old stuff?

857
01:23:09,053 --> 01:23:13,324
As if I knew it would take you
ten years to get married.

858
01:23:13,507 --> 01:23:16,176
And besides, it's your
auntie who brought them.

859
01:23:16,325 --> 01:23:17,678
Then let her wear them.

860
01:23:25,649 --> 01:23:29,753
It's very nice.
Look in the mirror.

861
01:23:35,530 --> 01:23:38,127
Come on, Nisrine, hurry up.

862
01:23:38,314 --> 01:23:40,259
I have something to tell you.

863
01:23:40,401 --> 01:23:42,346
So you know what to expect.

864
01:23:42,489 --> 01:23:45,265
You're no longer a child.

865
01:23:45,411 --> 01:23:49,230
I did well in bringing you up.

866
01:23:49,377 --> 01:23:53,719
But this is your last night at home.

867
01:23:54,666 --> 01:23:56,954
This separation breaks my heart.

868
01:23:57,101 --> 01:24:01,099
Tomorrow, it'll be your night.
You know what this means.

869
01:24:01,276 --> 01:24:03,423
You go from one stage to another.

870
01:24:03,572 --> 01:24:07,012
It will be the second stage of your life.

871
01:24:08,095 --> 01:24:10,171
All girls go through that.

872
01:24:10,322 --> 01:24:12,267
I've been through it too.

873
01:24:12,409 --> 01:24:15,327
You shouldn't be shy with him.

874
01:24:15,471 --> 01:24:18,875
He's your husband, your prince.

875
01:24:19,020 --> 01:24:22,045
For better or for worse.

876
01:24:22,220 --> 01:24:25,625
At first, it'll be difficult.
Then you'll get used to it.

877
01:24:25,770 --> 01:24:29,068
Slowly, you'll get to know him.

878
01:24:29,248 --> 01:24:32,926
That's life. Only God
knows what's in store.

879
01:24:33,076 --> 01:24:35,437
It's like a melon.

880
01:24:35,580 --> 01:24:38,498
You must cut it to see if it's good.

881
01:24:38,677 --> 01:24:41,833
God bless you.

882
01:24:41,983 --> 01:24:44,271
You'll always be my little girl.

883
01:24:44,417 --> 01:24:48,237
Stop, Mom, you'll make me cry.

884
01:24:48,384 --> 01:24:49,700
Don't forget, my darling.

885
01:24:49,845 --> 01:24:51,090
- Don't cry.
- You're my life.

886
01:24:51,237 --> 01:24:55,614
Our home will always be open for you.

887
01:24:55,760 --> 01:24:58,607
I'll always pray for you.

888
01:24:58,752 --> 01:25:00,696
- Let's go.
- Yes, love.

889
01:25:00,839 --> 01:25:04,659
- I don't want to see you cry.
- Alright, darling.

890
01:26:17,173 --> 01:26:19,878
Just a second.

891
01:26:20,234 --> 01:26:23,224
Just a second.
Sorry for interrupting.

892
01:26:23,400 --> 01:26:26,698
I'd like to present a small gift...

893
01:26:26,845 --> 01:26:28,505
...to the bride and the groom.

894
01:26:29,001 --> 01:26:31,741
A modest gift.

895
01:26:32,689 --> 01:26:36,793
<i>I don 't care what people say</i>

896
01:26:37,491 --> 01:26:40,611
<i>Your name is my prayer</i>

897
01:26:40,761 --> 01:26:44,794
<i>And fills me with Joy</i>

898
01:26:45,319 --> 01:26:52,377
<i>More beautiful than the earth, our love is</i>

899
01:26:53,008 --> 01:26:55,084
<i>They talk about love</i>

900
01:26:55,235 --> 01:26:58,355
<i>When they talk about you</i>

901
01:27:03,098 --> 01:27:06,218
<i>Love if you wish</i>

902
01:27:06,368 --> 01:27:09,357
<i>But love as they do...</i>

903
01:27:21,467 --> 01:27:23,828
Are you in line for the bathroom?

904
01:27:23,973 --> 01:27:25,004
Yes.

905
01:27:25,155 --> 01:27:28,073
May I go in before you?
I've got my period.

906
01:27:28,217 --> 01:27:31,242
No, no. Okay?

907
01:28:05,375 --> 01:28:07,948
Come on, girls.

908
01:28:19,605 --> 01:28:21,716
Ready?

909
01:28:28,964 --> 01:28:30,387
One...

910
01:28:38,288 --> 01:28:40,269
Two...

911
01:28:45,420 --> 01:28:46,772
Three!

912
01:28:51,544 --> 01:28:54,319
Look, it's a morning dove!

913
01:31:13,598 --> 01:31:16,718
To my Beirut

